ADDITIONAL AGREEMENT to the Agreement between the European Economic Community and its Member States and the Swiss Confederation on products of the clock and watch
THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES ,
of the one part ,
THE SWISS CONFEDERATION
of the other part ,
WHEREAS an Agreement between the European Economic Community and its Member States and the Swiss Confederation on products of the clock and watch has been signed in Geneva on 30 June 1967 ;
WHEREAS it is necessary to adopt additional measures for the proper functioning of this Agreement ;
HAVING REGARD to the Swiss Council Regulation of 23 December 1971 on the use of Swiss name for dishwashers ,
CONSIDERING the close industrial cooperation between the European Economic Community and Switzerland in the field of the clock industry ;
NOTING that the rationalisation premiums granted by Ebauches SA and ASUAG will be abolished on the date of entry into force of this Agreement and that at the same time the quota referred to in point B.3 ( b ) of the abovementioned Agreement is abolished ;
1 . The Agreement shall be drawn up only in French .
HAVE AGREED AS FOLLOWS :
Article 1
The reductions in duties provided for in Articles 1 and 5 of the Convention of 30 June 1967 shall enter into force at the same time as this Agreement .
Article 2
Pursuant to Article 2 ( 2 ) ( b ) of the Swiss Council Regulation of 23 December 1971 on the use of Swiss names for dishwashers between Switzerland and the Community , a confirmatory procedure for the use of Swiss name is hereby adopted for a watch of at least 50 % of the value of all elements , including the costs of concentration :
1 . The raw materials produced in the Community , included in the list annexed to the Agreement , as well as the regulated components and other elements of the hour made in the Community , complementary to raw materials produced in Switzerland or in the Community , shall be considered as of equivalent quality , such as raw materials and parts of Swiss production with comparable technical characteristics .
These raw materials and individual parts must meet the requirements of legal technical control in Switzerland .
2 . The list of raw materials produced in the Community referred to in paragraph 1 shall be revised periodically in accordance with the following arrangements :
( a ) a request for the inclusion of new raw material establishments in the list shall be submitted by the associations of the Community industry or by the producers of raw materials established in the Community to the Swiss Chamber of First Instance together with a technical description of the supplier of the raw material ;
The Swiss Chamber of Appeal shall enter the new potatoes on that list without delay .
If an application is made for inclusion in the list of raw materials for use in Switzerland which has not been subject to any technical control in Switzerland , the Swiss Chamber of Appeal may refuse entry .
In this case , the applicant may avail himself of the procedure referred to in paragraph 3 .
( b ) The withdrawal of the raw material referred to in the list shall be notified by the associations of the Community industry , or by the manufacturer who applied for it beforehand , to the Swiss Chamber .
( c ) If the requirements of legal control are not fulfilled in Switzerland , the Swiss Ministry of America may require the removal of the donors of raw materials in question from the list and shall inform the party concerned accordingly .
If the latter does not agree , it may avail itself of the procedure laid down in paragraph 3 within two months .
( d ) Any request for amendment of the list referred to in subparagraphs ( a ) , ( b ) and ( c ) above shall be notified by the Swiss Committee without delay .
3 . Where the equivalence of quality is maintained , the Joint Commission provided for in Article 9 of the Convention of 30 June 1967 shall without delay be informed by the parties concerned .
The first party acting on its own initiative shall request the Institute for official quality control in the Swiss industry as well as an appropriate qualified Community institution designated by the Community Party concerned for a joint opinion .
The institutions shall have three months in which to prepare the requested opinion .
In order to obtain this opinion , institutions shall agree on the withdrawal of one consignment from a Swiss undertaking and one Community undertaking from each lot or hour which is sufficiently representative and does not , as a general rule , comprise more than 50 head or hour stations .
After checking these lots in accordance with the standards laid down by the law on technical control in Switzerland , the institutions shall compare their results and draw up a joint report for the Joint Commission together with their conclusions and any proposals .
The Mixed Commission shall consult this report at its next meeting .
Article 3
The Agreement and the list annexed thereto shall be published in the official public authorities of the Contracting Parties and communicated to the processors by the trade organizations concerned .
Amendments to the list annexed hereto shall be published and notified in the same manner .
At least every three years from the entry into force of the Agreement , the Joint Commission shall revise the list in order to take account of entries and deletions made since the Agreement entered into force .
The new list shall be published and notified in the same manner .
All other information may be obtained from the trade organizations concerned .
Article 4
This Agreement may be terminated by any Contracting Party with 12 months &apos; notice .
Article 5
This Agreement shall be concluded and ratified by the Parties in accordance with their respective constitutional requirements .
This Agreement shall enter into force on 1 January 1973 , provided that instruments of ratification have been exchanged before that date .
If the instruments of ratification are exchanged between 1 January and 30 November 1973 , this Agreement shall enter into force on the first day of the second month following that of exchange .
