EUROPEAN AGREEMENT ON THE EXCHANGE OF REAGENCIES FOR THE GEOGRAPHICAL PURPOSES
THE MEMBER STATES OF THE EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT , which have signed this Agreement ,
tissue-typing reagents shall be available only in limited quantities .
Whereas it is highly desirable that Member States should assist one another in the purchase , if necessary , of such agents in a spirit of European solidarity ;
Whereas such mutual assistance is possible only if the nature and use of these tissue-typing reagents are subject to rules laid down jointly by the Member States and if the necessary facilities and exemptions are granted for the importation of such tissue-typing reagents ,
HAVE AGREED AS FOLLOWS :
Article 1
1 . For the purposes of this Convention , the expression &quot; tissue-typing reagents &quot; shall refer to all tissue-typing reagents of human , educational , plant and other origin used for tissue-typing .
2 . The provisions of Articles 2 to 6 of this Agreement shall also apply to cells of known antigenic composition to be used for the investigation of the reagents under consideration .
Article 2
The Contracting Parties undertake to make tissue-typing reagents available to other Contracting Parties requiring them , provided they have sufficient stocks for their own needs , to meet the costs of collection , preparation and transport and , where appropriate , their purchase price .
Article 3
tissue-typing reagents shall be made available to other Contracting Parties only on condition that no profit is attributable to them , that they are used only for medical and scientific , i.e. non-commercial , and that they are delivered only to laboratories designated by the Governments concerned in accordance with Article 6 of this Agreement .
Article 4
1 . The Contracting Parties shall ensure compliance with the provisions of the Protocol to this Agreement .
2 . They shall also respect the relevant international standard rules adopted by them .
3 . Each consignment of tissue-typing reagents shall be accompanied by a certificate to the effect that it has been prepared in accordance with the provisions of the Protocol .
This certificate shall conform to the model in the Annex to the Protocol .
4 . The Protocol and its Annex constitute an administrative arrangement which may be amended or supplemented by the Governments of the Parties to this Agreement .
Article 5
1 . The Parties shall take all necessary measures to exempt from all import duties the tissue-typing reagents placed at their disposal by other Parties .
2 . They shall also take all necessary measures to ensure that these substances are rapidly and most easily distributed to the consignees referred to in Article 3 of this Agreement .
Article 6
The Contracting Parties shall , through the Secretary-General of the Council of Europe , communicate to each other a list of national and / or regional reference laboratories authorised to issue certificates as provided for in Article 4 and to distribute imported tissue-typing reagents .
Article 7
1 . This Convention shall be open for signature by the Member States of the Council of Europe and may be signed by : ( a ) signature without reservation in respect of ratification or acceptance ; or
( b ) signature with reservation in respect of ratification or acceptance , followed by ratification or acceptance .
2 . Instruments of ratification or acceptance shall be deposited with the Secretary-General of the Council of Europe .
Article 8
1 . This Agreement shall enter into force one month after the date on which three Member States of the Council have become Contracting Parties in accordance with Article 7 .
