CUSTOMS AGREEMENT ON THE INTERNATIONAL TRANSPORT OF GOODS CARNETS TIR ( TIR AGREEMENT )
THE CONTRACTING PARTIES ,
DESIRING to facilitate the international transport of goods by road ,
CONSIDERING that the improvement of transport conditions is an essential factor in the development of cooperation between them ;
RECOGNISING the simplification and harmonization of administrative opportunities in international transport , in particular at frontiers ,
HAVE AGREED AS FOLLOWS :
CHAPTER I GENERAL PROVISIONS
( a ) Definitions
Article 1
For the purposes of this Convention : ( a ) &quot; TIR transport &quot; means the carriage of goods from one office of departure to a customs office of destination under the TIR procedure laid down in this Agreement ;
( b ) &quot; entry and exit duties &quot; means customs duties and any other charges , taxes , fees or other charges levied on or in connection with the importation or exportation of goods , but excluding fees and charges which are limited by approximately an amount to the cost of the services provided ;
( c ) &quot; road vehicle &quot; means not only road vehicles but also all trailers and semi-trailers intended to be towed from such vehicles ;
( d ) &quot; load emoluments &quot; means vehicles linked to each other and used as a unit for road transport ;
( e ) &quot; container &quot; means transport equipment ( when used , tank or other similar equipment ) which : ( i ) is a wholly or partly enclosed facility intended for the reception of goods ;
( ii ) of a permanent nature and therefore of sufficient suspicion to be used repeatedly ;
( iii ) specially designed to facilitate the transport of goods by one or more means of transport without transhipment of the contents ;
( iv ) constructed in such a way that it can be easily handled , particularly for the purpose of transhipment from one means of transport to another ;
( v ) constructed in such a way that it can be easily loaded and unloaded ; and
( vi ) has a minimum smoke content of one cubic metre ;
&apos;Restricted carcinemates` shall mean a container ;
( f ) &quot; customs office of departure &quot; means the customs office of a Contracting Party where the international transport operation starts under the TIR procedure for all loading or part loading ;
( g ) &quot; customs office of destination &quot; means the customs office of a Contracting Party at which international carriage under the TIR procedure ends on total loading or stowage ;
( h ) &quot; customs office of transit &quot; means the customs office of a Contracting Party through which a road vehicle , road train or container is imported or exported in the course of a TIR transport operation ;
( j ) &quot; persons &quot; means both natural and legal persons ;
( k ) &apos; goods normally serious or immovable goods` means all goods which , by reason of their weight , weight or characteristics , are not normally transported in a closed road vehicle or container ;
( l ) &quot; Guarantee association &quot; means an association approved by the customs authorities of one of the Contracting Parties to provide a guarantee to users of the TIR procedure .
( b ) Scope
Article 2
This Convention shall apply to goods transported by road vehicles , loads or containers , without transhipment through one or more frontiers from one customs office of departure of one Contracting Party to an office of destination for another Contracting Party , where transport by road , road or container takes place between the beginning and the end of the TIR journey .
Article 3
( a ) the transport of goods is effected : ( i ) by road vehicles , road trains or containers which have been registered beforehand in accordance with the conditions laid down in Chapter III ( a ) ; or
( ii ) other road vehicles , road trains or containers , provided that the conditions laid down in Chapter III ( c ) are met ;
( b ) the transport of goods is subject to the lodging of a guarantee by associations authorized under Article 6 and the transport is carried out under cover of a TIR carnet corresponding to the specimen given in Annex 1 .
( c ) Basic provisions
Article 4
Goods moving under the TIR procedure shall not be subject to payment or deposit at the offices of transit .
Article 5
1 . In principle , the examination at the offices of transit shall not take place for goods carried under the TIR procedure by road vehicles , road trains or containers .
2 . However , in order to prevent abuse , the customs authorities may , in exceptional cases and in particular where there is a presumption of irregularity , examine the goods at the offices of transit .
CHAPTER II EXPENDITURE INCURRED BY THE CARNETWORK ARTICLE FOR THE COUNTRIES
Article 6
1 . Each Contracting Party may , against collateral and under conditions to be laid down by it , grant authorization to associations , either themselves or through associations connected with them , to issue and accept the guarantee .
2 . An association shall be allowed in a country only if its guarantee covers liabilities arising from goods transported under cover of TIR carnets issued by foreign organizations belonging to the same international organization as the guaranteeing association .
Article 7
The TIR carnet forms sent to the guaranteeing associations by the foreign associations associated with them or by international organisations shall be exempt from import and export duties and from import or export prohibitions and restrictions on imports and exports .
Article 8
1 . The guaranteeing association must undertake to pay the relevant import or import duties plus any interest on account of late payment in accordance with the customs laws and other provisions in force in the country where an irregularity related to a TIR transport operation has been established .
The guaranteeing association shall be jointly and severally liable to the persons who are liable for the aforementioned amounts .
2 . Where the laws and regulations of a Contracting Party do not provide for the payment of import duties or other charges in the cases referred to in paragraph 1 , the guaranteeing association must , under the same conditions , undertake to pay an amount equal to the amount of such import or withdrawal duties plus any interest on late payment .
3 . Each Contracting Party shall set the maximum amount that may be required by the guaranteeing association in accordance with paragraphs 1 and 2 for each TIR carnet .
4 . The liability of the guaranteeing association vis-à-vis the authorities of the country of departure shall begin when the TIR carnet has been accepted by the customs office .
In the other countries through which the goods are still moving under the TIR procedure , the liability arising from the importation of the goods or from the acceptance of the TIR carnet by the customs office at which the TIR carnet is re-introduced when the TIR operation was suspended in accordance with Article 26 ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) .
5 . The liability of the guaranteeing association shall extend not only to the goods covered by the TIR carnet , but also to goods which are not covered by the TIR carnet but are placed under the customs seal of a part of the vehicle or container ; it shall not extend to other goods .
6 . The particulars contained in the TIR carnet concerning the goods shall be deemed to be correct for the determination of the duties referred to in paragraphs 1 and 2 , pending proof to the contrary .
7 . The competent authorities shall , as far as possible and when the amounts referred to in paragraphs 1 and 2 are due , require the person or persons directly liable before the guaranteeing association is called upon to pay them .
Article 9
1 . The guaranteeing association shall determine the period of validity of the TIR carnet , specifying the last day of validity after which the TIR carnet can no longer be presented for acceptance at the office of departure .
2 . Where the carnet referred to in paragraph 1 has been accepted by the office of departure at the latest until the last date of validity , it shall remain in force until the TIR transport operation is terminated at the office of destination .
Article 10
1 . The TIR carnet may be discharged with reservation or without reservation ; a reservation must relate to facts relating to the TIR transport itself .
These facts shall be recorded on the TIR carnet .
2 . Where the customs authorities of a country have issued a TIR carnet without reservation , they may no longer require the guaranteeing association to pay the amounts referred to in Article 8 ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) , unless the discharge certificate has been fraudulently or fraudulently obtained .
Article 11
1 . Where a TIR carnet has not been or has been discharged , the competent authorities may require the guaranteeing association to pay the amounts referred to in Article 8 ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) only if , within one year of the date of acceptance by the customs authorities of the TIR carnet , they have notified the guaranteeing association in writing of the non-discharge or discharge .
The same shall apply if the document of execution has been fraudulently or fraudulently obtained but in such cases the period shall be two years .
2 . The request for payment of the amounts referred to in Article 8 ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) shall be sent to the guaranteeing association not earlier than three months and not more than two years after the date of notification to the association that the carnet has not been or has been rendered subject to reservation , or that the certificate of discharge has been fraudulently or fraudulently obtained .
However , if the case has been brought within the aforementioned two-year period as a result of judicial proceedings , the request for payment shall be made within one year of the date on which the court decision has become final .
3 . The guaranteeing association shall pay the requested amounts within three months of the date of the request for payment .
The sums paid shall be reimbursed to the guaranteeing association if , within two years of the date of the payment requests , proof has been provided to the satisfaction of the customs authorities that an irregularity has not been committed in the transport operation in question .
CHAPTER III GOODS OF TRANSPORT WITH CARNETS TIR
( a ) Vehicles and containers
Article 12
Sections ( a ) and ( b ) shall apply only if each road vehicle satisfies , in respect of its construction and equipment , the conditions laid down in Annex 2 and has been registered in accordance with the procedure laid down in Annex 3 .
The classified information ( authorisation certificate ) shall conform to the model in Annex 4 .
Article 13
1 . The provisions of paragraphs ( a ) and ( b ) of this Chapter shall apply only if the vessels have been constructed in accordance with the conditions laid down in Annex 7 ( I ) and approved in accordance with the procedure laid down in Part II of that Annex .
2 . Containers admitted for the transport of goods under customs seal shall be presumed to comply with paragraph 1 and shall be recognized in accordance with the Customs Convention on container 1956 , with the conventions adopted for the purpose of the United Nations , with the 1972 Customs Convention on containers , or with any amended international agreement which may have been or may be established , and without further authorization for transport under the TIR procedure .
Article 14
1 . Each Contracting Party reserves the right not to recognise as valid the registration of road vehicles or vessels which do not comply with the requirements of Articles 12 and 13 .
However , the Contracting Parties shall avoid any delay in transport where the deficiencies found are negligible and there is no risk of fraud .
2 . No road vehicles or containers which no longer comply with the conditions for their registration may be re-used for the transport of goods under customs seal until their original condition has been restored or the vehicle or container has been re-registered .
( b ) Transport under cover of TIR carnets
Article 15
1 . No special customs document shall be required for the temporary importation of road vehicles , road trains or containers used for the transport of goods under the TIR procedure .
No guarantee shall be required in respect of road vehicles , road trains or containers .
2 . The provisions of paragraph 1 shall not prevent a Contracting Party from requiring the office of destination to carry out the formalities provided for by national law in order to ensure that the TIR transport operation is completed with a view to re-exporting the road vehicle , road train or container .
Article 16
Any road vehicle or articulated vehicle which carries out a TIR transport operation shall carry a lawful plate with the reference &apos; TIR &apos; in accordance with the specifications of Annex 5 .
These taflets shall be placed in such a way as to be easily visible , and they must be visible from them .
Article 17
1 . A separate TIR carnet shall be made out for each road vehicle or container .
However , an individual carnet may be made out for a load or for several containers loaded on a single road vehicle or a road train .
In such a case , the TIR carnet shall indicate separately the contents of each vehicle or vessel to which a load is to be attached .
2 . The TIR carnet shall be valid for one journey only .
It shall contain at least the number of sections which can be separated and the sections which are necessary for the transport in question .
Article 18
A TIR transport operation may be carried out through several offices of departure and destination ; if no other arrangement has been made by the Contracting Party or Contracting Parties concerned : ( a ) the offices of departure must be situated in the same country ;
( b ) the offices of destination may not be more than two different countries ;
( c ) the total number of offices of departure and destination shall not exceed four .
Article 19
The goods and the road vehicle , the lorry or containers shall be presented at the office of departure under cover of the TIR carnet .
The customs authorities of the country of origin shall take the necessary measures to satisfy themselves as to the accuracy of the manifest and to establish seals or to verify the persons under their responsibility .
Article 20
The customs authorities may set a time limit for the journey by their country and may require the road vehicle , road train or container to carry a prescribed itinerary .
Article 21
The road vehicle , road train or container shall be presented with the corresponding TIR carnet for inspection at each office of transit and at the office of destination .
Article 22
1 . The offices of transit of each Contracting Party shall , as a general rule , recognize the final accounts of goods received from the customs authorities of the other Contracting Parties , except where examination of the goods in accordance with Article 5 ( 2 ) is carried out .
However , where necessary for control purposes , the customs authorities may also lodge their own seals .
2 . Seals accepted as such by a Contracting Party shall enjoy on their territory the same legal protection as that afforded by national customs seals .
Article 23
The customs authorities may , in exceptional cases only : - allow road vehicles , road trains or containers to be accompanied at the expense of the transporter ,
- carry out checks in the course of the journey and an inspection of the loading of goods by road vehicles , road tankers and containers .
Article 24
Where the customs authorities carry out an examination of the consignment of goods by road , road or loading or container at a transit office or in the course of the journey , they shall record on the carnet sections of the TIR carnet used in their country the corresponding master sheets and on the tranches remaining under the TIR carnet the newly landed seals and the type of check carried out .
Article 25
In cases other than those referred to in Articles 24 and 35 where seals are broken in the course of the journey or where goods are destroyed or damaged without breach of customs seal , the rules on use of the TIR carnet and the Protocol annexed to the TIR carnet shall be included in Annex 1 , without prejudice to national legislation .
Article 26
1 . Where a transport operation carried out under cover of a TIR carnet takes place on a part of the territory of a State which is not a Contracting Party to this Agreement , the TIR operation shall be suspended during the transit through that territory .
In such a case , the customs authorities of the Contracting Party through whose territory the goods are subsequently transported shall accept the TIR carnet , provided that the seals and / or identification marks have remained intact , for the purpose of continuing the TIR transport operation .
2 . The same shall apply to that part of the journey on which the TIR carnet holder does not use the carnet in the territory of a Contracting Party because the simplified procedures are available for the customs transit operation or the use of such a procedure is not required .
3 . In such cases , where the TIR operation is suspended or re-introduced , the customs offices of transit shall be considered as office of departure or office of transit upon arrival .
Article 27
Subject to the provisions of this Agreement , and in particular Article 18 thereof , the customs office of destination originally indicated may be replaced by another customs office of destination .
Article 28
On arrival of the cargo at the office of destination , the TIR carnet shall be discharged immediately , provided that the goods are placed under another customs procedure or released for free circulation .
( c ) Provisions relating to the transport of goods in excess of those normally large or immovable property
Article 29
1 . This Section shall apply only to the transport of goods of exceptional or impaired nature as defined in Article 1 ( k ) .
2 . For the purposes of this Section , goods in exceptional cases may be carried in vehicles or containers without customs seal , depending on the decision of the office of departure .
3 . The provisions of this Section shall apply only if , in the opinion of the customs office of departure , the nature of the goods usually serious or impaired and of the containers which may be carried it can be easily identified by means of an existing description or can be stamped with a customs seal or identification mark so that they cannot be replaced or removed without clear evidence .
Article 30
Any provisions of this Convention , of which the special provisions of this section do not derogate , shall also apply to the transport of goods , in exceptional cases , in serious or impaired form , under the TIR procedure .
Article 31
The liability of the guaranteeing association shall extend not only to goods covered by the TIR carnet but also to goods which are not covered by the TIR carnet but are on the loading area or between the goods covered by the TIR carnet .
Article 32
The TIR carnet used must bear the words &quot; extremely serious or impaired goods &quot; in envelopes and on each section in English or French language .
Article 33
The office of departure may require loading lists , photographs , plans , etc . , which are necessary for the identification of the goods carried to be attached to the TIR carnet .
In that case , it shall stamp those documents and attach a copy to the reverse side of the TIR carnet , and shall enter them in all the manifests .
Article 34
The offices of transit of each Contracting Party shall accept the seals and / or identification marks affixed by the competent authorities of the other Contracting Parties .
They may , however , also bear additional seals and / or identification marks , but shall show on the carnet sections of the TIR carnet used in their country , on the corresponding master sheets and on the remaining sections of the TIR carnet the newly affixed seals and / or identification marks .
Article 35
Where the customs authorities require customs clearance or identification marks to be removed at a customs office of transit or in the course of the journey on account of an examination of the goods on the goods , they shall record on the carnet sections of the carnet IR used in their country , on the corresponding master sheets and on the sections of the TIR carnet the newly affixed customs declarations and / or marks .
CHAPTER IV ACTIVITIES
Article 36
Any person who infringes the provisions of this Convention shall be liable to penalties in accordance with the legislation of the country in which the offence was committed .
Article 37
Where it is not possible to determine where the irregularity has been committed , it shall be deemed to have been committed in the territory of the Contracting Party in which it was established .
Article 38
1 . Each Contracting Party shall have the right to provisionally or permanently exclude from the facilities provided for in this Agreement a person who is guilty of serious breach of customs legislation or regulations governing the international transport of goods .
2 . Such exclusion must be notified immediately to the customs authorities of the Contracting Party in whose territory the person concerned has his domicile or place of business and to the guaranteeing association or associations in the country where the offence or irregularity was committed .
Article 39
The Contracting Parties shall not take account of minor discrepancies in the implementation of the obligations relating to the period and the route .
2 .
Also , differences between the particulars contained in the TIR carnet manifest and the contents of the road vehicle , road train or container shall not be regarded as infringements of the carnet holder within the meaning of this Convention if it is demonstrated to the satisfaction of the competent authorities that those derogations are not based on errors found in connection with the loading or dispatch of the goods or the completion of the manifest .
Article 40
The customs administrations of the country of departure and of the country of destination shall not apply any derogations found therein to the carnet holder where those derogations relate to customs procedures which took place before or after the TIR transport operation and to which the holder of the carnet was not involved .
Article 41
Where it is established to the satisfaction of the customs authorities that the goods covered by the TIR carnet manifest have been lost , have been irretrievably lost , or have been irretrievably lost , because of their nature , by natural weaknesses and circumstances , exemption from the duties and taxes normally applicable shall be granted .
Article 42
Upon a reasoned request by a Contracting Party , the competent authorities of the Contracting Parties affected by a TIR operation shall provide all available information necessary for the application of Articles 39 , 40 and 41 .
CHAPTER V SUPPLEMENTARY DOCUMENTS
Article 43
The Explanatory Notes in Annex 6 and Annex 7 , Part III , provide interpretations of certain provisions of this Agreement and its Annexes .
They shall also return to some recommended practices .
CHAPTER VI MISCELLANEOUS
Article 44
Each Contracting Party shall grant to the guaranteeing associations concerned facilities for the transfer of the necessary means of payment : ( a ) to pay the amounts claimed by the authorities of the Contracting Parties pursuant to Article 8 ; and
( b ) the payment for the TIR carnet forms sent to the guaranteeing associations by the foreign associations associated with them or by international organisations .
Article 45
Each Contracting Party shall publish a list of offices of departure , offices of transit and offices of destination authorised to carry out TIR transport operations .
Less-favoured Contracting Parties shall agree on the corresponding border customs posts and the hours of operation thereof , by mutual agreement .
Article 46
1 . No fee shall be levied on the official acts of the customs authorities provided for in this Agreement unless such acts are performed outside the normal days , hours or places specified for that purpose .
2 . The Contracting Parties shall , as far as possible , facilitate the customs clearance of perishable goods at customs offices .
Article 47
1 . This Agreement shall not preclude the restrictions or controls provided for by national rules on grounds of public moral , public safety , public health , veterinary or phytosanitary measures , nor shall it preclude the levying of fees to be levied in accordance with those rules .
2 . This Convention shall not preclude the application of other national transport rules .
Article 48
This Agreement shall not preclude Contracting Parties which form part of a customs or economic union from adopting or implementing special provisions applicable to the transport of goods effected in their territories , provided that such provisions do not restrict the facilities provided for in this Agreement .
Article 49
This Agreement shall not preclude the application , at present or in the future , of more extensive facilities which the Contracting Parties may lend either through unilateral provisions or through two or more bilateral agreements , provided that such facilities do not impede the application of this Agreement , and in particular the implementation of TIR transport operations .
Article 50
Upon request , the Contracting Parties shall provide each other with the information necessary for the application of this Agreement , and in particular with regard to the registration of road vehicles and containers and their design characteristics .
Article 51
The Annexes to this Convention shall form an integral part thereof .
CHAPTER VII FINAL PROVISIONS
Article 52
Signature , ratification , acceptance , approval and accession
1 . All States which are members of the United Nations or of any of their specialized agencies or of the International Atomic Energy Agency , or Parties to the Statute of the International Court of Justice , and any other State invited by the General Assembly of the United Nations , may become Parties to this Agreement : ( a ) by signing it without reservation in respect of ratification , acceptance or approval ;
( b ) deposit an instrument of ratification , acceptance or approval after signature , subject to ratification , acceptance or approval ; or
( c ) by depositing an instrument of accession .
2 . This Convention shall be open to the United Nations Bureau in Geneva from 1 January 1976 to 31 December 1976 .
It shall be open for signature thereafter .
3 . Pursuant to paragraphs 1 and 2 , customs and economic unions may also become Contracting Parties to this Agreement at the same time as all their Member States or at any time after all their Member States have become Contracting Parties .
However , these Unions do not have the right to vote .
4 . Instruments of ratification , acceptance , approval or accession shall be deposited with the Secretary-General of the United Nations .
Article 53
Entry into force
1 . This Agreement shall enter into force six months after the date on which five States referred to in Article 52 ( 1 ) have signed it without reservation in respect of ratification , acceptance or approval , or have deposited their instrument of ratification , acceptance , approval or accession .
2 . After five States referred to in Article 52 ( 1 ) have signed the Agreement without reservation in respect of ratification , acceptance or approval , or having deposited their instrument of ratification , acceptance , approval or accession , it shall enter into force for all new Contracting Parties six months after the date on which they have deposited their instrument of ratification , acceptance , approval or accession .
3 . Any instrument of ratification , acceptance , approval or accession deposited after the entry into force of an amendment to this Agreement shall be deemed to have been deposited in respect of this Agreement , as amended .
4 . Any such instrument which is deposited after the adoption of an amendment but before its entry into force shall be deemed to have been deposited on the date of entry into force of the amendment to this Agreement , as amended .
Article 54
Denunciation
1 . Any Contracting Party may denounce this Agreement by notifying the Secretary-General of the United Nations .
2 . Such denunciation shall take effect fifteen months after the date of receipt by the Secretary-General of the United Nations of such notification .
3 . The termination of the TIR carnet shall not affect the validity of the TIR carnet accepted by an office of departure before the date on which denunciation takes effect , nor shall the liability of the guaranteeing associations remain under the conditions laid down in this Convention .
Article 55
Entry into force
If , after the entry into force of this Agreement , the number of States Parties is less than five for 12 consecutive months , this Agreement shall cease to apply at the end of that period of 12 months .
Article 56
Implementation of the TIR Convention in 1959
1 . This Agreement shall , upon its entry into force , terminate and replace the TIR Convention 1859 in relations between the Contracting Parties .
2 . Classification ( registration certificate ) issued under the conditions laid down in the TIR Convention of 1959 for road vehicles and containers shall be recognised by the Contracting Parties to this Convention for the transport of goods under customs seal within their period of validity or subject to renewal , provided that the vehicles and containers continue to comply with the conditions under which they were originally registered .
Article 57
Settlement of disputes
1 . Any dispute which may arise between two or more Contracting Parties with respect to the interpretation or application of this Agreement shall be settled by negotiation between them or by any other means .
2 . Any dispute between two or more Contracting Parties concerning the interpretation or application of this Agreement which cannot be resolved in the manner provided for in paragraph 1 of this Article shall be submitted , at the request of one of them , to an arbitral tribunal composed as follows : each of the parties to the dispute shall appoint an arbitrator ; the two arbitrators shall appoint another arbitrator as arbitrator .
If , three months after the receipt of the request , one of the parties has not appointed an arbitrator , or if the arbitrators have not yet elect a chairman , either of them may request the Secretary-General of the United Nations to appoint an arbitrator or a Chairman of the arbitral tribunal .
3 . The decision of the arbitral tribunal constituted in accordance with paragraph 2 shall be binding on the parties to the dispute .
4 . The arbitral tribunal shall adopt its own rules of procedure .
5 . The arbitral tribunal shall take a decision by majority vote .
6 . Any dispute which may arise between the parties to the dispute as a result of the interpretation and implementation of the arbitration decision may be referred for decision by either party to the arbitral tribunal which issued the award .
Article 58
Reservations
1 . Any State may declare , at the time of signature , ratification or accession , that it is not bound by Article 57 ( 2 ) to ( 6 ) .
The other Contracting Parties shall not be bound by these paragraphs in respect of any Contracting Party making such a reservation .
2 . Any Contracting Party which makes a reservation under paragraph 1 may at present withdraw it by notifying the Secretary-General of the United Nations * .
3 . With the exception of the reservations provided for in paragraph 1 , no reservation may be made in respect of this Agreement .
Article 59
Procedures for amending this Agreement
1 . This Convention may be amended with its Annexes on a proposal from a Contracting Party in accordance with the procedure laid down in this Article .
2 . Any proposal for an amendment to this Agreement shall be examined by a Management Committee composed of all the Contracting Parties in accordance with the rules of procedure set out in Annex 8 .
Any such proposed amendment , considered or prepared at the meeting of the Management Committee , and adopted by the Committee by a two-thirds majority of its members present and voting , shall be communicated for approval to the Contracting Parties by the Secretary General of the United Nations .
3 . Any proposed amendment communicated to it in accordance with paragraph 2 of this Article shall enter into force for all Contracting Parties three months after the expiry of a period of 12 months from the date of the communication , if , during that period , no State Contracting Party has notified an objection to the proposed amendment to the Secretary-General of the United Nations .
4 . If an objection to a proposed amendment has been notified in accordance with paragraph 3 , the amendment shall be deemed not to be adopted and shall remain unaffected .
Article 60
Special procedures for amending Annexes 1 , 2 , 3 , 4 , 5 , 6 and 7
1 . Any proposal for an amendment to Annexes 1 , 2 , 3 , 4 , 5 , 6 and 7 which has been considered in accordance with Article 59 ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) shall enter into force on the date of the adoption of the proposal unless the Management Committee , at an earlier date fixed at the same time as the Management Committee , has the same opportunity , has notified , or five of those States , whichever is the smaller , the Secretary-General of the United Nations that they raise objections to the amendment .
The data referred to in this paragraph shall be determined by the Management Committee by a two-thirds majority of its members present and voting .
2 . The amendment adopted in accordance with paragraph 1 of this Article shall replace , for all Contracting Parties , all previous provisions to which it relates .
Article 61
Requests , communications and objections
The Secretary-General of the United Nations shall inform all Contracting Parties and all States referred to in Article 52 ( 1 ) of any requests , notifications and objections made pursuant to Articles 59 and 60 and of the date of entry into force of any amendment .
Article 62
Review conference
1 . A State which is a Contracting Party may , by notifying the Secretary-General of the United Nations , require the convening of a conference for the revision of this Convention .
2 . A review conference to which all Contracting Parties and all States referred to in Article 52 ( 1 ) are invited shall be convened by the Secretary-General of the United Nations if , within six months of the date on which the Secretary-General of the United Nations has made the notification , at least one-quarter of the States which are Contracting Parties notify him of their acceptance with the agreement of the request .
3 . A review conference to which all Contracting Parties and all States referred to in Article 52 ( 1 ) are invited shall be convened by the Secretary-General of the United Nations , even if the Management Committee has notified a request to that effect .
The Management Committee shall decide by a majority of its members present and voting whether such a request should be addressed to the Secretary-General of the United Nations .
4 . When a conference is convened in accordance with paragraphs 1 or 3 , the Secretary-General of the United Nations shall inform all Parties accordingly and invite them to submit within three months the proposals to be considered at the conference .
The provisional agenda and the text thereof shall be forwarded by the Secretary-General of the United Nations to all Contracting Parties at least three months before the beginning of the Conference .
Article 63
Notifications
In addition to the notifications and notifications referred to in Articles 61 and 62 , the Secretary-General of the United Nations shall notify all States referred to in Article 52 : ( a ) the signatures , ratifications , assumptions , approvals and accessions referred to in Article 52 ;
( b ) the dates of entry into force of this Agreement in accordance with Article 53 ;
( c ) the termination referred to in Article 54 ;
( d ) the entry into force of this Agreement in accordance with Article 55 ;
( e ) the reservations referred to in Article 58 .
Article 64
Authentic texts
After 31 December 1976 , the original of this Agreement shall be deposited with the Secretary-General of the United Nations , who shall send certified copies thereof to all Contracting Parties and to all States not Contracting Parties referred to in Article 52 ( 1 ) .
